newsitem.title: USA: Nebraska fed cattle at $119-$120/dressed - trade.
newsitem.headline: Nebraska fed cattle at $119-$120/dressed - trade.

text.p: Nebraska feedlot cattle near midday Wednesday were trading in light volume steady to $1.00 per cwt higher at $119.00 to $120.00 per cwt on a dressed basis, market sources said.
About 3,000 to 4,000 head sold near midday to one major Nebraska packer, they said.
Prices were not established on a live basis, with no bids reported. Owners were asking $74.00/live.
Feedlots were working through the week's showlist, with USDA near midday estimating 56,000 head sold for the week to date. Showlists were pegged near 65,000 head.
